The paper focuses on designing a vision system for autonomous micro-robots, which involves robotics (cs.RO) and computer vision (cs.CV) aspects. The system is a synthetic neural network, which suggests the involvement of neural networks (cs.NE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of decision-making mechanisms for invoking proper robot behaviors, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY).
